Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.
When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} to the water and cook until tender,
~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop
them sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips. Quarter the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Drain the
@king prawns{150%g}. Once hot, add the prawns, sliced pepper and sliced
@mushrooms{180%g}(sliced). Fry until slightly charred and soft,
~{5-6%minutes}. Continue to stir while it cooks. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Add the garlic and @red Thai style paste{50%g} to the pan. Cook until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Add the @soy sauce{15%ml}, @ketjap manis{50%g} and @water{50%ml} (see pantry for
amount) to the veg. Stir together, then add the @mangetout{80%g} and cook until
the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles through the fragrant sauce and toss until well combined.
Add a good squeeze of lime. Taste and season with salt and pepper or more lime
if you feel it needs it.

Share the sticky Thai style noodles between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the
@salted peanuts{25%g} and coriander. Serve with any remaining lime wedges for
squeezing over to finish. Enjoy!